artifact_name: rosette bowl(?); lotus bowl(?); bird bowl(?)
Description: Rim fragment of North Ionian pottery cup (lotus bowl, bird bowl or rosette bowl); interior glazed with two added red and perhaps one added white line; exterior: set of at least five thick verticals; band below.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.860)
